    <description>
        <div>
            <p>The Secretary of State established a Policy Planning Staff, with a Director who held
                rank equivalent to an Assistant Secretary of State, on May 5, 1947. Between 1955 and
                1961, the head of the Policy Planning function served as Assistant Secretary of
                State for Policy Planning, one of ten Assistant Secretaries authorized by Congress
                in the Department of State Organization Act of Aug 5, 1955 (P.L. 84-250; 69 Stat.
                536). From 1961 to 1966, the Counselor of the Department served as Chairman of the
                Policy Planning Council. Since 1966, the Secretary of State has designated the head
                of the Policy Planning function under several different titles at a rank equivalent
                to an Assistant Secretary of State.</p>
        </div>
    </description>
